Remarks
. This species is distinguished from its congeners by the combination of the following characters: 
1
) left mandible with three small teeth on inner edge, right with two small tooth (

Fig. 

9


I–J); 
2
) dark coarser setae on the posterior margin of abdominal sternite VIII; 
3
) pear-like aedeagus with apical paired sclerites; 
4
) outer capsule of spermatheca swollen.
